data.text: "Honor, Homeland, Valor, Discipline." These are still the four tenets that define the Marine Nationale — or "La Royale" — as one of the world's oldest navies. The Marine Nationale was instrumental in establishing the French colonial empire and engaging in near-constant conflicts with their European neighbors, particularly the Royal Navy.
